Automated SOC Lab: End-to-End Threat Detection & Response
Overview
This repository documents the implementation of a full-scale, automated Security Operations Center (SOC) lab. The project bridges the gap between threat detection and incident response by automating the analysis and escalation of critical security alerts. By integrating a SIEM, SOAR platform, Threat Intelligence, and a Case Management system, this lab demonstrates a significant reduction in Mean Time to Respond (MTTR) and mitigates analyst alert fatigue.

Features
Real-time Threat Detection: Uses Wazuh (SIEM) to monitor and identify malicious activity, such as SSH brute-force attacks.

SOAR Automation: Orchestrates the entire workflow using Shuffle (SOAR), removing manual steps.

Threat Intelligence Enrichment: Automatically queries the VirusTotal API for attacker IP reputation and malicious scores.

Conditional Alert Escalation: Implements customizable logic to prioritize high-fidelity threats and reduce noise.

Case Management & Alerting: Automatically generates actionable alerts in TheHive for analysts and sends instant email notifications.

System Architecture

Data Flow: Kali Linux (Attacker) → Ubuntu Server (Wazuh Agent) → Wazuh Manager (SIEM) → Shuffle (Webhook) ↔ VirusTotal (Enrichment) → TheHive (Case) & Email (Notification)

Technical Stack
OS: Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS (Docker Host), Kali Linux (Attacker)

SIEM: Wazuh

SOAR: Shuffle

Threat Intelligence: VirusTotal API (v3)

Case Management: TheHive 5

Notifications: Email (SMTP)

Virtualization: VirtualBox, Docker Compose

Usage / Demo
To see the automation in action, simulate a brute-force attack from the Kali Linux VM:

Bash
# Example SSH brute-force command using hydra
hydra -l [user] -P [password_list] ssh://[target_ip]
What Happens Next:
1 Wazuh Agent detects the failed login attempts.

2 Wazuh Manager triggers rule 5712.

3 Shuffle receives the alert via webhook and enriches it with VirusTotal data.

4 Shuffle evaluates the conditional logic (e.g., reputation < 0).

5 Check TheHive Alerts dashboard for the new, enriched alert.

6 Check your configured email inbox for the notification.
